			<h2>Stop Treating Each Marketing Platform The Same</h2>

			<p>
				One of the biggest mistakes businesses make is they use the same skills and strategies on different platforms.  The techniques and content you use for Twitter probably will not work on another platform.  The way you engage with a potential customer at your office would probably be different than at a festival or social event.
				</p>
				<p>
				How you analyze and calculate the results for each platform will be different as well.  Its important to know which data points to focus on with each marketing platform.  We can teach your team what to focus on and how to get better results.
				<p>
